An Eastern Cape school principal, who is accused of beating a 14-year-old pupil with a sjambok, appeared in court yesterday. Cofimvaba Village School principal Mzukisi Mdlankomo, 53, appeared at the Cofimvaba Magistrate s Court facing a charge of assault with intent to do grievous bodily harm for allegedly assaulting Siyavuya Mapapu. Mapapu is a Grade 7 pupil at the school.NPA regional spokesman, Luxolo Tyali, said that Mdlankomo made a brief appearance and the case was postponed to January 19 for the accused to get a lawyer and for further investigation. The accused was released on warning, said Tyali.Provincial education spokesman, Malibongwe Mtima, said the department was informed of the teacher s arrest. In fact, we, the department, was supposed to have started our internal investigation on Friday, but the principal was not at school. So now that he has been released on warning we will start with our internal processes this week, said Mtima. lulamilef@dispatch.co.za